com.lightstreamer.adapters.remote.log

Interface Logger


  • public interface Logger
    Interface to be implemented to consume log from the library.
    Instances of implemented classes are obtained by the library through the LoggerProvider instance set on Server.SetLoggerProvider.

      • getIsDebugEnabled

        boolean getIsDebugEnabled()
        Checks if this logger is enabled for the Debug level.
        This property is intended to lessen the computational cost of disabled log Debug statements. Note that even if the property is false, Debug log lines may be received anyway by the Debug methods.
        Returns:
        true if this logger is enabled for Debug events, false otherwise.
